# ✅ Personal Habit Tracker

A clean and minimal habit tracking web application built with **pure HTML, CSS, and JavaScript**.

Track your daily habits, build consistency, monitor weekly progress, and maintain streaks—all without any backend or external dependencies. Everything is stored locally in your browser using **localStorage**.

---

## ✨ Features

- ➕ Add new habits
- 🎯 Set target frequency for each habit
- ✅ Mark habits as completed each day
- 📅 Weekly progress grid
- 🔥 Automatic streak counter
- 💾 Data persistence with localStorage
- 🎨 Clean, modern, and responsive UI
- ⚡ No installation required

---

## 🚀 Demo

Simply open the HTML file in your browser.

No build tools.

No frameworks.

No dependencies.

---

## 🛠️ Built With

- HTML5
- CSS3
- Vanilla JavaScript
- localStorage API

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
.
├── index.html
└── README.md
```

Everything lives inside a single HTML file, making the project extremely portable and easy to customize.

---

## 💡 How It Works

1. Add a habit.
2. Choose its target frequency.
3. Check it off whenever you complete it.
4. Watch your weekly progress update automatically.
5. Build longer streaks by staying consistent.

Your data is automatically saved in **localStorage**, so refreshing or reopening the browser won't erase your habits.

---

## 🎨 Design

The interface focuses on simplicity and usability.

- Light color palette
- Rounded cards
- Soft shadows
- Modern typography
- Responsive layout
- Minimal distractions

---

## 📦 Local Storage

All data is stored locally in your browser.

No accounts.

No servers.

No cloud database.

No internet connection required after loading the page.

